844
00:55:57,705 --> 00:55:58,705
What?

845
00:55:59,080 --> 00:56:00,122
It's nothing.

846
00:56:03,663 --> 00:56:04,997
Can I look around your place?

847
00:56:05,080 --> 00:56:06,080
Of course.

848
00:56:08,788 --> 00:56:09,788
Be careful.

849
00:56:12,039 --> 00:56:13,955
Playing games, reading comics

850
00:56:14,039 --> 00:56:15,497
and working out at home.

851
00:56:15,872 --> 00:56:17,413
So that's why you're a homebody.

852
00:56:18,121 --> 00:56:19,622
I'm busy all night.

853
00:56:20,246 --> 00:56:21,580
But what's this?

854
00:56:21,663 --> 00:56:22,747
Why haven't you opened it?

855
00:56:23,371 --> 00:56:24,371
What is it?

856
00:56:26,080 --> 00:56:27,413
Oh, that?

857
00:56:27,997 --> 00:56:29,788
It's a rare Superman item.

858
00:56:30,163 --> 00:56:32,121
I haven't even opened it
because I'm afraid I'll break it.

859
00:56:33,580 --> 00:56:34,580
Do you want to see it?

860
00:56:34,663 --> 00:56:35,663
Oh, no.

861
00:56:35,747 --> 00:56:37,246
It's okay if you want to see it.

862
00:56:37,330 --> 00:56:39,288
No. I'm scared I'll break it.

863
00:56:39,622 --> 00:56:41,705
- It's really okay.
- Come to think of it...

864
00:56:43,121 --> 00:56:44,663
you're like Superman.

865
00:56:45,246 --> 00:56:46,538
- Me?
- Yeah.

866
00:56:46,872 --> 00:56:48,747
Superman wears glasses

867
00:56:48,830 --> 00:56:51,330
and a suit to work.

868
00:56:51,413 --> 00:56:53,288
All serious and stern.

869
00:56:53,538 --> 00:56:56,663
But when he takes off his glasses,
the female character can't recognize him.

870
00:56:57,205 --> 00:56:59,663
My first impression of you was

871
00:57:00,121 --> 00:57:02,497
that you were very serious and stern.

872
00:57:02,747 --> 00:57:03,997
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

873
00:57:04,079 --> 00:57:06,830
But on the train
without your glasses and smiling

874
00:57:06,914 --> 00:57:08,455
you looked so different.

875
00:57:11,872 --> 00:57:12,872
- Yu-mi
- Yes?

876
00:57:13,330 --> 00:57:14,663
Then, as you said

877
00:57:14,747 --> 00:57:16,622
I'll throw away
all the glasses I have at home.

878
00:57:16,914 --> 00:57:19,039
Hey! No, that's not it.

879
00:57:19,121 --> 00:57:21,663
It's because it's a twist.

880
00:57:21,747 --> 00:57:23,163
You wear glasses at work.

881
00:57:23,246 --> 00:57:25,538
So with glasses, you're Kent Clark

882
00:57:25,622 --> 00:57:27,288
and when you take them off,
you're Superman.

883
00:57:27,371 --> 00:57:29,747
So I'm dating Superman.

884
00:57:29,830 --> 00:57:30,872
But Superman's name

885
00:57:31,413 --> 00:57:32,997
isn't Kent Clark, it's Clark Kent.

886
00:57:34,163 --> 00:57:35,163
It's Kent Clark.

887
00:57:35,288 --> 00:57:36,288
It's Clark Kent.

888
00:57:36,580 --> 00:57:37,705
I'm the one who bought this.

889
00:57:37,955 --> 00:57:39,330
Oh, Soon-rok.

890
00:57:40,121 --> 00:57:41,872
It's Kent Clark.

891
00:57:41,955 --> 00:57:43,622
- Want to make a bet?
- Fine, sure.

892
00:57:43,705 --> 00:57:46,371
Do what you want. You can flick my
forehead or something.

893
00:57:46,455 --> 00:57:48,246
- No going easy.
- Of course not.

894
00:57:48,580 --> 00:57:49,580
Okay.

895
00:57:50,371 --> 00:57:51,413
Jeez.

896
00:57:52,914 --> 00:57:53,914
Here.

897
00:57:54,205 --> 00:57:55,705
It's Clark Kent.

898
00:57:57,163 --> 00:57:58,246
I was right, wasn't I?

899
00:57:58,455 --> 00:57:59,455
Come here.

900
00:58:00,413 --> 00:58:01,580
A bet is a bet.

901
00:58:02,038 --> 00:58:03,038
Wait...

902
00:58:03,121 --> 00:58:04,371
Hold on...

903
00:58:04,872 --> 00:58:05,872
Present your forehead.

904
00:58:23,538 --> 00:58:24,580
So cute.

905
00:58:30,163 --> 00:58:31,205
Did it hurt?

906
00:58:33,413 --> 00:58:36,371
- It hurt, right? Hit me back.
- No, it's okay.

907
00:58:36,455 --> 00:58:38,330
- It's okay, really.
- No, it's fine.

908
00:58:38,413 --> 00:58:40,330
- Really. Just hit me once.
- It's okay. It was a bet.

909
00:58:40,413 --> 00:58:41,788
It's okay. Give me a good one.

910
00:58:44,705 --> 00:58:45,705
Go ahead and hit me... Ugh!

911
00:58:50,413 --> 00:58:51,955
- Let's play the game, Soon-rok.
- Okay, but...

912
00:58:52,038 --> 00:58:53,038
Yeah, let's play a round.

913
00:58:53,246 --> 00:58:55,538
- You hit me too hard...
- That's the one from before, right?

914
00:58:55,622 --> 00:58:56,872
Virtual reality.

915
00:58:56,955 --> 00:58:59,038
Yu-mi, let's stop playing the game

916
00:58:59,663 --> 00:59:01,497
- and go see a movie instead.
-A movie?

917
00:59:02,163 --> 00:59:03,747
Did you book movie tickets?

918
00:59:03,830 --> 00:59:05,914
Did you think we were
just going to play games?

919
00:59:06,788 --> 00:59:07,788
Let's go.

920
00:59:08,330 --> 00:59:09,872
- Okay.
- Hurry.

921
00:59:17,205 --> 00:59:19,121
Since you're such a big Superman fan

922
00:59:19,497 --> 00:59:21,705
it's the original version.

923
00:59:22,038 --> 00:59:24,288
Really? Where is it playing?

924
00:59:36,205 --> 00:59:37,246
Let's see.

925
00:59:38,205 --> 00:59:40,580
Row J, seats six and seven.

926
00:59:43,663 --> 00:59:45,288
Oh, this is the theater?

927
00:59:46,205 --> 00:59:47,246
Huh? Here it is.

928
00:59:47,413 --> 00:59:48,580
Yu-mi, over here.

929
00:59:50,121 --> 00:59:52,371
So this is how you have fun at home.

930
00:59:52,705 --> 00:59:55,413
Goodness, this is a tough vibe to match.

931
00:59:55,497 --> 00:59:56,538
Just play along.

932
00:59:56,622 --> 00:59:58,663
Our boyfriend is from Generation MZ.

933
01:00:02,330 --> 01:00:04,205
What are you doing? Over here.

934
01:00:05,246 --> 01:00:06,246
But...

935
01:00:07,163 --> 01:00:09,205
there's no one else in the theater.

936
01:00:11,079 --> 01:00:12,288
I rented out the whole place.

937
01:00:13,663 --> 01:00:14,830
This whole place?

938
01:00:15,205 --> 01:00:16,205
Renting a theater

939
01:00:16,705 --> 01:00:17,705
is nothing...

940
01:00:19,330 --> 01:00:20,330
for me.

941
01:00:23,163 --> 01:00:25,246
Is this a "rich family's
youngest son" concept?

942
01:00:26,830 --> 01:00:28,663
And compared to that,
you're a poor writer.

943
01:00:30,622 --> 01:00:34,330
For me to fall for you
and even rent a theater...

944
01:00:38,538 --> 01:00:39,538
is just ridiculous.

945
01:00:43,038 --> 01:00:44,038
What on earth...

946
01:00:46,913 --> 01:00:50,413
about you made me like this?

947
01:00:52,830 --> 01:00:54,705
Well, it must be my pretty face.

948
01:00:56,288 --> 01:00:57,330
You're not wrong.

949
01:01:05,580 --> 01:01:07,205
I think the ice cream delivery is here.

950
01:01:11,829 --> 01:01:13,413
Oh, ice cream.

951
01:01:16,538 --> 01:01:17,538
Ta-da!

952
01:01:18,205 --> 01:01:19,622
Why is there so much?

953
01:01:19,705 --> 01:01:21,163
They're all different flavors.

954
01:01:21,330 --> 01:01:22,538
Twelve flavors.

955
01:01:22,622 --> 01:01:24,954
But isn't this too much?

956
01:01:25,038 --> 01:01:26,038
I ordered extra

957
01:01:26,121 --> 01:01:27,705
since you were coming.

958
01:01:28,079 --> 01:01:29,330
I was worried it wouldn't be enough.

959
01:01:29,455 --> 01:01:32,330
I'm just worried you spent too much money.

960
01:01:32,413 --> 01:01:34,205
It's okay. Let's eat before it melts.

961
01:01:36,913 --> 01:01:39,371
This isn't the kind of ice cream
you can get just anywhere.

962
01:01:40,996 --> 01:01:41,996
Especially...

963
01:01:43,705 --> 01:01:44,913
in the middle of a mountain like this.

964
01:01:54,954 --> 01:01:56,787
Wolves might be drawn by the smell.

965
01:01:57,288 --> 01:01:58,455
Let's finish it all.

966
01:02:03,996 --> 01:02:05,038
Soon-rok.

967
01:02:06,163 --> 01:02:07,580
I lose all track of time

968
01:02:07,663 --> 01:02:09,246
when I'm with you.

969
01:02:17,246 --> 01:02:18,288
Did you hear that?

970
01:02:18,871 --> 01:02:19,871
Yeah.

971
01:02:20,871 --> 01:02:22,580
- I think it came from over there.
- You're right.

972
01:02:41,538 --> 01:02:42,871
Who would've known

973
01:02:42,954 --> 01:02:44,913
that Shin PD was this kind of person.

974
01:02:45,996 --> 01:02:47,038
He's cute.

975
01:02:52,996 --> 01:02:54,038
Soon-rok.

976
01:02:56,413 --> 01:02:57,455
Where'd he go?

977
01:03:06,038 --> 01:03:07,038
Who is it?

978
01:03:07,580 --> 01:03:08,580
Delivery.

979
01:03:11,913 --> 01:03:12,913
Soon-rok?

980
01:03:14,829 --> 01:03:15,871
Soon-rok?

981
01:03:18,330 --> 01:03:19,330
What was that?

982
01:03:19,413 --> 01:03:20,913
This is your house.
Why did you ring the doorbell?

983
01:03:21,079 --> 01:03:22,079
Soon-rok?

984
01:03:22,871 --> 01:03:24,038
What are you talking about?

985
01:03:25,246 --> 01:03:26,413
I'm here...

986
01:03:26,497 --> 01:03:28,288
to deliver the waffles.

987
01:03:29,288 --> 01:03:31,288
A deliveryman this time?

988
01:03:31,746 --> 01:03:33,079
Don't you think leftover ice cream

989
01:03:33,163 --> 01:03:35,038
would go well with the waffles?

990
01:03:36,497 --> 01:03:38,497
Good idea. Thank you for the delivery.

991
01:03:39,746 --> 01:03:41,497
So how should I pay?

992
01:03:42,455 --> 01:03:43,455
With a kiss?

993
01:03:56,871 --> 01:03:57,913
What?

994
01:03:57,996 --> 01:04:00,662
You're really addicted to role-playing.

995
01:04:01,497 --> 01:04:03,413
You should've been the writer, not me.

996
01:04:03,497 --> 01:04:04,538
Just a moment.

997
01:04:05,455 --> 01:04:06,455
Thanks.

998
01:04:11,121 --> 01:04:12,497
I'm sorry, Master.

999
01:04:14,079 --> 01:04:15,371
I dozed off...

1000
01:04:15,455 --> 01:04:16,913
and didn't realize you called.

1001
01:04:17,538 --> 01:04:19,622
When did I call you?

1002
01:04:19,954 --> 01:04:21,330
I didn't ask for you.

1003
01:04:22,038 --> 01:04:23,038
No.

1004
01:04:23,121 --> 01:04:24,121
You did.

1005
01:04:28,330 --> 01:04:31,413
I have restored all
of Master's health and mana.

1006
01:04:35,829 --> 01:04:37,163
This looks delicious.

1007
01:04:37,913 --> 01:04:40,371
I'm full, but since we're eating,
let's finish it.

1008
01:04:41,580 --> 01:04:42,621
One moment.

1009
01:04:53,455 --> 01:04:54,871
TONGUE CELL

1010
01:04:54,954 --> 01:04:56,538
Don't be so nervous.

1011
01:04:56,621 --> 01:04:58,996
Not at all. I'm always ready.

1012
01:05:04,455 --> 01:05:05,580
There's no need to be nervous.

1013
01:05:05,746 --> 01:05:06,913
It's not your first time.

1014
01:05:09,079 --> 01:05:11,455
Of course. But today's mission

1015
01:05:11,538 --> 01:05:13,205
could be a very long one.

1016
01:05:13,580 --> 01:05:15,455
The kiss is always ready.

1017
01:05:16,038 --> 01:05:17,038
The hard part...

1018
01:05:18,079 --> 01:05:20,621
- Yeah.
- It's all about timing.

1019
01:05:23,913 --> 01:05:25,746
Gosh, you should have called.

1020
01:05:27,121 --> 01:05:28,288
No, I'll go now.

1021
01:05:28,371 --> 01:05:29,371
I'll be right there.

1022
01:05:30,538 --> 01:05:32,662
Yeah, I'm in the neighborhood.

1023
01:05:33,163 --> 01:05:34,163
At a book cafe.

1024
01:05:35,413 --> 01:05:37,371
Okay, I'll be right there.

1025
01:05:39,662 --> 01:05:40,746
Where are you going?

1026
01:05:40,829 --> 01:05:41,829
I'm so sorry.

1027
01:05:41,913 --> 01:05:44,205
My parents are at my place.

1028
01:05:44,662 --> 01:05:45,996
Right... right now?

1029
01:05:46,079 --> 01:05:48,288
Yeah, they showed up unannounced.

1030
01:05:48,371 --> 01:05:49,704
They said they're just
dropping off kimchi.

1031
01:05:51,038 --> 01:05:52,079
I should go.

1032
01:06:02,829 --> 01:06:03,913
That's my dad's car.

1033
01:06:04,704 --> 01:06:05,704
I see.

1034
01:06:06,621 --> 01:06:07,996
It's better if I go from here.

1035
01:06:08,621 --> 01:06:09,621
Okay.

1036
01:06:15,537 --> 01:06:16,537
Get home safe.

1037
01:06:17,205 --> 01:06:18,621
- I'll call you.
- Okay.

1038
01:06:20,163 --> 01:06:21,413
- I'll get going.
- Bye.

1039
01:06:27,704 --> 01:06:28,704
Go.

1040
01:06:38,871 --> 01:06:39,954
Go.

1041
01:06:40,246 --> 01:06:41,246
Bye.

1042
01:07:15,996 --> 01:07:18,163
Yu-mi's gone now.

1043
01:07:18,662 --> 01:07:20,746
I wanted to hang out with her all night.

1044
01:07:49,330 --> 01:07:50,954
WRITER KIM YU-MI

1045
01:07:55,288 --> 01:07:56,371
Yu-mi.

1046
01:07:56,579 --> 01:07:57,954
What are you doing? Were you asleep?

1047
01:07:58,246 --> 01:07:59,246
No.

1048
01:07:59,829 --> 01:08:02,829
My parents just left
after dropping off kimchi.

1049
01:08:04,163 --> 01:08:05,205
I see.

1050
01:08:06,537 --> 01:08:07,537
Want to come over?

1051
01:08:11,038 --> 01:08:12,412
If you're tired, we meet tomorrow.

1052
01:08:12,496 --> 01:08:13,496
I'm on my way.

1053
01:08:14,246 --> 01:08:15,246
I'll be right there.

1054
01:08:53,330 --> 01:08:56,913
But then I remembered
I forgot the carrots.

1055
01:08:56,996 --> 01:09:00,412
So I called my mom to ask if she
really needed the carrots

1056
01:09:00,496 --> 01:09:03,246
but she insisted that she needed them
and told me to buy them.

1057
01:09:03,496 --> 01:09:04,537
So, what could I do?

1058
01:09:04,621 --> 01:09:06,121
The moment she finishes her sentence

1059
01:09:06,454 --> 01:09:07,746
I'll jump into the empty space.

1060
01:09:07,829 --> 01:09:11,454
So I went, and what?
The supermarket was closing.

1061
01:09:11,537 --> 01:09:12,787
They wouldn't let me in.

1062
01:09:12,871 --> 01:09:15,704
So I begged and pleaded...

1063
01:09:15,954 --> 01:09:18,829
The problem is that's still one sentence.

1064
01:09:19,038 --> 01:09:20,704
I rushed in, saying sorry

1065
01:09:20,787 --> 01:09:22,621
and quickly grabbed the carrots.

1066
01:09:23,038 --> 01:09:24,496
This isn't working. Let's cut her off.

1067
01:09:24,579 --> 01:09:26,496
There's no other way but to interrupt her.

1068
01:09:27,412 --> 01:09:30,537
What if we interrupt the conversation
and initiate an emergency kiss?

1069
01:09:30,621 --> 01:09:32,412
My mom was buying carrots.

1070
01:09:32,496 --> 01:09:33,704
She said I was the one to buy them...

1071
01:09:33,787 --> 01:09:35,454
No. It's too risky.

1072
01:09:35,871 --> 01:09:37,370
The distance is too great.

1073
01:09:37,454 --> 01:09:38,913
We could break

1074
01:09:38,996 --> 01:09:40,537
the wine glass.

1075
01:09:40,913 --> 01:09:42,621
- Did you know?
- What?

1076
01:09:43,038 --> 01:09:45,746
Most of my missions are adventures.

1077
01:09:53,288 --> 01:09:55,205
Tasting to see if it's salty...

1078
01:09:55,288 --> 01:09:56,746
Damn, it's so salty.

1079
01:09:58,454 --> 01:10:00,121
Checking the battery's charge

1080
01:10:00,205 --> 01:10:01,829
is also an adventure.

1081
01:10:02,288 --> 01:10:03,288
That's so absurd, right?

1082
01:10:03,370 --> 01:10:04,871
So I said to my mom, "Mom, no..."

1083
01:10:07,829 --> 01:10:08,871
I'm afraid of adventure...

1084
01:10:10,370 --> 01:10:14,287
but no one can do this but me!

1085
01:11:20,079 --> 01:11:21,704
How many people in the world would know

1086
01:11:22,871 --> 01:11:25,245
what kind of person Soon-rok really is?

1087
01:11:58,245 --> 01:12:00,245
YUMI'S CELLS 3

1088
01:12:00,329 --> 01:12:01,787
You said you wanted to go to Kyoto, right?

1089
01:12:01,871 --> 01:12:03,662
Did you see who just walked by?

1090
01:12:03,746 --> 01:12:04,746
Hello, Yu-mi?

1091
01:12:04,829 --> 01:12:07,496
Don't you think
we should tell the Chief Editor?

1092
01:12:07,579 --> 01:12:10,329
Soon-rok's principles are his identity.

1093
01:12:10,621 --> 01:12:11,829
A fist-sized face!

1094
01:12:11,913 --> 01:12:14,787
Skin as fair as snow!

1095
01:12:14,871 --> 01:12:16,412
I object to this!

1096
01:12:17,121 --> 01:12:18,954
- Let go!
- Watch out!

1097
01:12:19,038 --> 01:12:21,038
I can wait.

1098
01:12:21,121 --> 01:12:24,079
The reason love is always surprising

1099
01:12:24,162 --> 01:12:27,954
is because no two loves are ever the same.
